                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5045/127: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-07-13T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1925—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>146. Your 268, July 10, 6 p.m. You are authorized, if need be in consultation
                    with the Chinese authorities, to reconsider the status of the administration of
                    the International Settlement at Shanghai as now constituted under existing
                    regulations with a view to the definite establishment of the Settlement upon a
                    basis eliminating any possibility of doubt that the diplomatic representatives
                    have an authority commensurate with their international responsibilities. London
                    informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
